description:
&lt;p&gt;We currently have an exciting &lt;strong&gt;placement opportunity &lt;/strong&gt;within the &lt;strong&gt;Berkshire NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/strong&gt; which will allow the successful candidate to gain &lt;strong&gt;regular shifts&lt;/strong&gt; and valuable &lt;strong&gt;experience&lt;/strong&gt; within a unique environment. We are currently recruiting for a talented Community Psychiatric Nurse who shares the Trusts’ vision to be on the leading edge of healthcare for the benefit of their patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Locations covered: &lt;/strong&gt;Nicholsons House, Maidenhead. Please note that you may be required to work at or from any additional location as may be determined by the Trust from time to time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6 – example rate:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Day Rate - £20.35 per hour&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Night/Sat Rate - £26.16 per hour&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sun/Bank Holiday Rate - £31.97 per hour&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours and shifts:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;18 hours per week&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shifts to be agreed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The responsibilities of the post-holder are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To work effectively individually and as part of a multi-disciplinary team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To develop and maintain specialist knowledge of nursing practice, relevant to the clinical area&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To be responsible for the care of assigned patients and to manage, direct and evaluate their care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To provide high standards of nursing care, reflecting the beliefs of professional nursing practice and patient care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To undertake physical health monitoring&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To involve and encourage the patient’s family and friends to be actively involved in the caring process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To communicate effectively to and with the patient, relatives, carers and colleagues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To escalate as required, reporting any incidents/accidents and ensuring they are recorded using the appropriate method&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To complete and maintain accurate patient care records on the electronic patient management system&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To conduct themselves in a professional manner at all times&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In order to apply for a post you &lt;strong&gt;must&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have previous experience working in a Mental Health care setting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have knowledge of Mental Health legislation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have good oral and written communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be able to work effectively as part of a team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be able to evidence continuing professional development and a desire to undertake further training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return for your hard work and your professional, caring and reliable service you will have access to the following benefits:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive, weekly pay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to the NHSP Stakeholder Pension&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid annual leave and statutory maternity pay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Registration with NHS Professionals is subject to employment history and reference checking and offers of registration are therefore conditional upon the receipt of satisfactory references.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a placement opportunity but an extension may be offered to the right candidate.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Haven&#39;t found what you&#39;re looking for? Email the team at BerkshireHealthcare@NHSProfessionals.nhs.uk to ask about joining the bank of flexible workers so that you can find shifts to suit you!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
